<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: No movement in footer with scrolling.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=5064&amp;p=8041#p8041"><![CDATA[
Hello,<br /><br />You can control scrolling by using one of those CSS properties: <span style="font-style: italic">overflow-x, overflow-y, overflow</span>.<br />To disable vertical scrolling, apply <span style="font-style: italic">overflow-y</span> property to <span style="font-style: italic">body</span> element:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>body {<br />  overflow-y: hidden;<br />}<br /></code></dd></dl><br /><br />To stick footer to the bottom of the site, you have to set its <span style="font-style: italic">position</span> CSS property to <span style="font-style: italic">fixed</span>, and then <span style="font-style: italic">bottom</span> property to <span style="font-style: italic">0px</span>:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>footer {<br />   position: fixed;<br />   bottom: 0px;<br />}<br /></code></dd></dl><br /><br />I made a working demo, check it out here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://dabblet.com/gist/3666448">http://dabblet.com/gist/3666448</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3621">d.szlachta</a> — Fri Sep 07, 2012 1:58 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
